  "Title": "FileBrowser Quantum has Username Enumeration via Authentication Timing Side-Channel",
  "Description": "The `/api/auth/login` authentication endpoint does not execute in constant time. When a non-existent username is supplied, the server returns a `401`/`403` response almost immediately. When a valid username is provided, the server performs a bcrypt password comparison, causing a measurable delay in the response time.",
